Kenya has been reelected to the International Civil Aviation Organisation Council for a three-year term.Speaking shortly after the reelection, the Kenya Civil Aviation Authority director general Gilbert Kibe said being on the ICAO council is important to Kenya as the country can directly participate in shaping policy and the future of aviation globally. Kenya is honoured by the ICAO member states for the confidence they have shown in us which was demonstrated by the overwhelming support during the elections, he said. Kenya got 159 votes out of 172, the highest number of votes among the African candidates.